page.title: 17A bit of West Malling
page.content:
During the week 8th - 12th July I went to Leybourne and West Malling to take part in a survey. I was in Mrs. Gibson's group. When we went to West Malling we passed a Dentist, a Post Office, a couple of take-away food shops, two food shops, five non-food shops, one bank, one restaurant and one cafe. We also passed a load of pubs, bars, inns, a hotel and a club for Working Men. We saw one chapel, one abbey, one railway station, five houses, a plastics firm, two lots of rough grazing land, one field of crops, an Estate Agent, a Solicitors and a playgroup.
- Samantha C.-
